        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued September 4 at 5:07PM PDT until September 4 at 6:15PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 507 PM MST, Doppler radar indicated that thunderstorms have ended
across the warned area. However, between 1 and 1.5 inches of rain
have already fallen and flash flooding is likely occurring or
expected to begin shortly.

HAZARD...Life-threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Life-threatening flash flooding of low-water crossings,
creeks, normally dry washes and roads.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Pierce Ferry And Antares Roads and Dolan Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.

In hilly terrain there are hundreds of low water crossings which are
potentially dangerous in heavy rain. Do not attempt to cross flooded
roads. Find an alternate route.</instruction>
